casebody.data:
People ex rel. Julius W. Smith v. Ionia Circuit Judge. A complainant taking testimony is not bound in the first instance to pay the expense of the cross-examination. Sawyer v. Sawyer, Walk Ch., 48, approved. Per Curiam. W. 0. Webster for the motion. H. B. Carpenter against.

Commissioner’s charges for talcing cross-examination.

Mandamus to order commissioner to return proofs.

Motion submitted June 18.

Granted June 19.
